# Asha PM Project

Asha PM Project is a web-based project management application built with TypeScript, Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL. It provides features for managing projects, tasks, teams, and users.

## Features

- Create, update, and delete projects
- Assign tasks to projects
- Assign tasks to teams and users
- Manage teams and team members
- User authentication and authorization
- API endpoints for interacting with the application

## Prerequisites

To run this application locally, you need to have the following installed:

- Node.js: [Download and install Node.js](https://nodejs.org)
- PostgreSQL: [Download and install PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org)

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/asha-pm.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:

 ```bash 
 cd asha-pm-project
 ```

3. Install the dependencies:

````bash
npm install
````

4 .Set up the database:

- Create a PostgreSQL database.
- Update the database configuration in the .env file with your PostgreSQL database details.
- Run the application:

```bash
npm start
```

 - The application will start running at http://localhost:8082.


## API Documentation
The API documentation is available at http://localhost:8082/api-docs when the application is running. It provides detailed information about the available endpoints and their usage.

